						 <p>Noting that a recent edit by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lordblaze" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3951547&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1524258121" alt="LordBlaze" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3951547)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lordblaze" >LordBlaze</a></span> was reverted, as it was unnecessary.</p> <p>&quot;Pathfinding&quot; is considered an acceptable word, and is widely-used as such:</p> <ul> <li><a href="http://www.dictionary.com/browse/pathfinding">http://www.dictionary.com/browse/pathfinding</a></li> <li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathfinding">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathfinding</a></li> <li><a href="https://www.thefreedictionary.com/pathfinding">https://www.thefreedictionary.com/pathfinding</a></li> </ul> <p>Editors, when making spelling fixes, please be sure that the changes you introduce are necessary.</p> 
